#Text=Prague/East bank of Vltava
#Text=The East of Prague is on the east side of the Vlatava River beside the Old Town and New Town districts .
#Text=It consists of the numbered districts of Praha 3 , Praha 10 , Praha 11 and Praha 12 .
#Text=Most of the sites listed are in the Casadral district of Žižkov , which roughly corresponds to Praha 3 .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Like many districts of the city , Prague 3 is socioeconomically diverse .
#Text=The western part of Žižkov is known for its high concentration of brothels , strip clubs and cheap bars .
#Text=Yet only a short distance away are nice apartments and a new shopping mall with expensive stores .
#Text=Historically , Žižkov was a rough , working-class neighborhood , filled with factories , brothels and gambling bars .
#Text=Often compared to the Paris neighborhood of Montmartre , Žižkov today is an economically diverse neighborhood filled with Czech families , expats teaching English and working artists .
#Text=Žižkov is said to have more bars per capita than any other neighborhood in the world .
#Text=Praha 10 is an old district in Prague .
#Text=Žižkov
#Text=Prague 3 is served by the metro line A| , which stops at Jiřího z Poděbrad , Flora , and Želivského .
#Text=However , through the heart of Žižkov ( oldest part of the quarter with most hotels and restaurants )
#Text=go trams
#Text=9 ( it takes just around 10 minitus from " Vodičkova " station on Wenceslas square ) , 5 and 26 and other areas of Žižkov also trams 1 , 10 , 11 and 16 .
#Text=Vinohrady
#Text=Stops Náměstí míru ( " Peace Square " ) or Jiřího z Poděbrad and trams 4 , 10 , 11 , 16 and 22 .
#Text=Karlín
#Text=Stops Florenc and Křižíkova and Invalidovna .
#Text=Trams nr. 3 and 8 .
#Text=Vršovice
#Text=No metro connection , but you can go to Náměstí míru and then use tram 4 or 22 .
#Text=Trója

#Text=The fastest way to get to Troja is to take subway to station Nádraží Holešovice ( you can get there also by several tram or bus lines ) and from there continue with bus 112 or the dedicated free ZOO bus ( on weekends in the season ) to the station Zoo Praha .
#Text=This station is just between the zoo and castle , to get to the botanical garden , follow the marked way uphill ( 5-10 minutes ) .
#Text=Alternatively , from May to October , you can take a steamboat from the city center ( Rašínovo nábřeží ) .
#Text=If you happen to be in the peninsula area of Praha 7 , especially around the Royal Game Preserve or Výstaviště , it can be a nice walk or a bike ride .
#Text=North

#Text=Northern areas of Prague are accessible via Palmovka ( Praha 8 , southern part of Libeň quarter ) , or via station Nádraží Holešovice ( Praha 7 , quarter Holešovice , transit to Pendolino trains ) , Kobylisy or Ládví ( Praha 8 , quarter Ďáblice - nearly northernmost part of Prague ) .
#Text=Žižkov
#Text=Žižkov Television Tower , Mahlerovy sady 1 , Praha 3 , ☏ +42267005778 , ✉ info@tower.cz .
#Text=10AM-11PM every day .
#Text=Built by the communists to jam foreign radio signals , the most hideous building in Prague offers spectacular views of the city .
#Text=The cafe at the top is a great place to grab a coffee and enjoy the view .
#Text=Lookout for the giant metallic alien babies that have been added to the tower .
#Text=Admission is 230Kč ( December 2017 ) for adults .
#Text=National Memorial on the Vítkov Hill ( Národní památník na Vítkově ) .
#Text=" Žižkov Monument " , located at the top of Vítkov Hill .

#Text=This immense equestrian statue was erected in 1950 to commemorate Czech national hero Jan Žižkov , who fought his most famous battle on this site and later had the hill and the neighbouring city renamed after himself .
#Text=The scale of the monument is impressive enough , but the views of Žižkov ( and entire Prague ) from the top of the hill really make the climb worthwhile .
#Text=Military Museum ( Armádní muzeum ) , U Památníku 2 , Praha 3 , ☏ +420973204924 .
#Text=10AM-6PM .
#Text=Closed for reconstruction until 2020 .
#Text=Showcases the uniforms , weapons , artifacts , and maps relating to the Czechoslovak armed forces during World Wars I and II .
#Text=Interactive exhibitions on the World Wars from the Czechoslovakian perspective .
#Text=Free entrance .
#Text=Not recommended for young children due to shocking content ( war crimes a. o. ) .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Church of the Most Sacred Heart of Our Lord ( Kostel Nejsvětějšího Srdce Páně ) , náměstí Jiřího z Poděbrad ( metro line A , station " Jiřího z Poděbrad " ) .
#Text=Porbably the most unusual and monumental modern church dominates the big Jiřího z Poděbard Square .
#Text=Built between 1928 and 1932 and designed by the Slovene architect Jože Plečnik .
#Text=Candidate to get on UNESCO list .
#Text=For modern architect lovers , this is definitely a must !
#Text=After the visit , you can buy something on popular farmer 's market nearby .
#Text=Cemeteries
#Text=New Jewish Cemetery .
#Text=Olšany Cemetery , Vinohradska 153 , ☏ +420267310652 , ✉ olsany@hrbitovy.cz .
#Text=8:00-19:00. After day in a busy city , walking in calm and big Olšany Cemetery is a great idea !
#Text=It is the largest graveyard in Prague , remarkable for many art nouveau monuments .
#Text=The cemetery has calm and mysterious atmosphere , some perts of it are very old .

#Text=Famous people such as Jan Palach ( in protest against apathy of poeple in communism self-immolated student ) , Klement Gottwald ( first communist president of Czechoslovakia ) , 19th century writer Karel Havlíček Borovský , actors Rudolf Hrušínský and Jan Werich and many others are buried here .
#Text=free .
#Text=Old Olšany Jewish Cemetery , Fibichova ( Used since late 18th century , when well-know Old Jewish Cemetery in Old Town stopped to be used .
#Text=One century later , bigger New Cemetery was built ( see above ) .
#Text=Located right under the Žižkov TV Tower , more than half of the cementary was destroyed .
#Text=At least , the oldest part remained ) , ☏ +420221711511 .
#Text=Mo , We 11:00 - 15:00 , Fri 9:00 - 13:00 , it 's possible to arrange your visit on a different date .
#Text=50 Kč .
#Text=Troja
#Text=Three of the main attractions of Prague - Troja ( the zoo , the botanical garden , and the castle ) are close to each other and make a great opportunity for a day trip .
#Text=To save entrance costs , buy Trojská karta ( Troy Card ) .
#Text=The price is 250 Kč for adults , 130 Kč for children and 650 Kč for families ( two adults and two children ) .
#Text=It also offers free entry to some bonus actions by these attractions .
#Text=You can buy the Troy Card at ticket offices of these attractions or in the ticket office of Pražská paroplavební ( Prague steamship company ) .
#Text=Prague Zoo ( Zoo Praha ) , U Trojského zámku 3/120 .
#Text=Founded in 1931 , it is well known for its significant contribution to saving many species , most notably the Przewalski horse .
#Text=In 2008 Forbes Traveler Magazine listed Prague Zoo as the 7th best in the world .
#Text=The zoo occupies 45 hectares ( 111 acres ) and houses over 5000 animals that represent 674 species from all around the world ( as of December 31 , 2008 ) .
#Text=There is also a chairlift in the zoo .
#Text=Prague Botanical Garden ( Botanická zahrada Praha ) .
#Text=Open air exhibitions including historical vineyard of St. Claire and Japanese garden .
#Text=Tropical greenhouse Fata morgana .
#Text=Each year in spring an exhibition of living butterflies .
#Text=Troja Palace ( Trojský zámeček ) .
#Text=Baroque chateau with garden and art exhibitions .
